Analysis: Let $x+y+z=t$, since $x+2 y+3 z=1$, we have $\left\{\begin{array}{c}x+y=t-z \\ x+2 y=1-3 z\end{array} \Rightarrow\left\{\begin{array}{l}x=2 t+z-1 \\ y=1-t-2 z\end{array}\right.\right.$;
Thus, $z(t-z)+(2 t+z-1)(1-t-2 z)=-1$,
Simplifying, we get: $3 z^{2}-(3-4 t) z+2 t^{2}-3 t=0$, since the discriminant is not less than 0, hence
