-4 \leqslant x \leqslant-3.5
\end{array} \Leftrightarrow x=\frac{2-3 \sqrt{11}}{2} .\right.\right.
\end{aligned}
$$

Thus, the equation has two roots: $x=\frac{2-3 \sqrt{11}}{2}$ and $x=5$.

